@startuml
!include ../../styles/plantuml-theme.puml
title Online Store operational feedback loop
top to bottom direction
scale 750 width
skinparam nodesep 20
skinparam ranksep 24
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
actor Customer
rectangle "Checkout service\nAPI, order state and\npayment-provider dependency" as Service #DDEBF7
rectangle "Telemetry and objectives\nTraces | metrics | logs | SLI/SLO" as Signals #E2F0D9
rectangle "Actionable alert\nNamed owner and runbook" as Alert #FFF2CC
rectangle "Customer support\nCase and escalation" as Support #FFF2CC
rectangle "Owned incident response\nDiagnose, limit harm, communicate" as Response #FCE4D6
rectangle "Restore and validate\nService and data state" as Restore #E2F0D9
rectangle "Incident and problem learning\nEvidence, cause hypotheses, actions" as Learn #E4DFEC
rectangle "Architecture records\nModels, risks and ADRs" as Architecture #D9EAD3
rectangle "Governed change\nTest, deploy and measure" as Change #D9EAD3
Customer --> Service : uses checkout
Service --> Signals : emits redacted telemetry
Signals --> Alert : evaluates actionable condition
Alert --> Response : routes to service owner
Customer --> Support : reports visible problem
Support --> Response : escalates with case evidence
Response --> Restore : mitigates and restores
Restore --> Service : returns acceptable service
Response --> Learn : preserves incident evidence
Restore --> Learn : records validation results
Learn --> Architecture : updates material assumptions
Architecture --> Change : informs approved change
Change --> Service : deploys and measures
legend bottom
Solid arrows show operational evidence, response and feedback.
SLI = service-level indicator; SLO = service-level objective.
ADR = Architecture Decision Record.
endlegend
@enduml
